1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,039
Characters, actions, places, occupations, and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

2
00:00:07,039 --> 00:00:10,697
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

3
00:00:10,697 --> 00:00:13,136
Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:16,032 --> 00:00:21,578
Thank you all for coming
to my birthday party today.

5
00:00:21,578 --> 00:00:23,779
Enjoy yourselves, everyone.

6
00:00:23,779 --> 00:00:25,055
Enjoy yourselves.

7
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:35,248
North.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,185
Why are you avoiding me?

9
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:39,667
Hi, Pai.

10
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,109
When did you get here—

11
00:00:41,608 --> 00:00:43,337
Why aren’t you wearing red?

12
00:00:43,711 --> 00:00:45,023
Don’t you know it’s not auspicious?

13
00:00:45,597 --> 00:00:46,787
I forgot.

14
00:00:51,555 --> 00:00:52,445
Put this on.

15
00:00:52,869 --> 00:00:54,203
We don’t want anyone scolding you.

16
00:00:56,275 --> 00:00:57,438
Thank you.

17
00:01:09,358 --> 00:01:10,766
That’s so romantic.

18
00:01:11,415 --> 00:01:13,553
He’s proposing in front of
our whole family,

19
00:01:14,177 --> 00:01:15,939
and on Grandpa’s birthday, too.

20
00:01:16,538 --> 00:01:17,909
Grandpa must be so surprised.

21
00:01:18,658 --> 00:01:20,031
Grandpa already knew about it.

22
00:01:23,376 --> 00:01:24,245
What do you mean?

23
00:01:24,619 --> 00:01:26,380
It’s a strategic marriage.

24
00:01:27,703 --> 00:01:30,067
Their family is a
gas station franchise owner,

25
00:01:30,541 --> 00:01:33,189
and our family owns
a convenience store chain.

26
00:01:33,489 --> 00:01:38,850
Eventually, our convenience stores
will be available at all their gas stations.

27
00:01:41,246 --> 00:01:42,242
For someone like us, North,

28
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:47,803
marriage is just something
that is arranged to benefit both families.

29
00:01:48,801 --> 00:01:49,823
Ugh.

30
00:01:50,347 --> 00:01:52,682
You’re so unromantic, Pai.

31
00:01:54,155 --> 00:01:56,972
I don’t think it’s just for business, though.

32
00:01:57,396 --> 00:01:58,836
They agree to get married, after all.

33
00:02:00,184 --> 00:02:01,713
I’m sure they must have feelings
for each other, at least.

34
00:02:07,654 --> 00:02:08,958
I’d like to hope so.

35
00:03:19,211 --> 00:03:24,822
I must, once again, congratulate
our family’s newest couple.

36
00:03:25,072 --> 00:03:26,373
Once you tie the knot,

37
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:29,823
make me proud and
have children right away.

38
00:03:31,396 --> 00:03:33,890
And thank you, all of you,

39
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,070
for coming to my birthday party today.

40
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:43,164
How glad I am to see our family prosperous and expanding.

41
00:03:43,314 --> 00:03:47,515
I hope you will all continue
to work hard to fulfill your duties.

42
00:03:47,515 --> 00:03:51,913
It puts my mind at ease
to see our family doing so well.

43
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:54,260
Happy birthday.

44
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,625
Happy birthday, Grandpa.

45
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:56,984
- Happy birthday, Papa.
- Happy birthday.

46
00:03:56,984 --> 00:03:57,772
Thanks.

47
00:03:58,870 --> 00:04:00,201
Pai.

48
00:04:01,075 --> 00:04:03,394
You’ve been managing our shopping mall
for a while.

49
00:04:03,943 --> 00:04:04,824
How is it going?

50
00:04:04,974 --> 00:04:05,912
It’s been great, Grandpa.

51
00:04:06,311 --> 00:04:09,901
We’re reshuffling our marketing strategy
to fit with new customers.

52
00:04:10,251 --> 00:04:12,310
I believe the numbers will turn out better
by the end of the year.

53
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:12,810
I see.

54
00:04:14,757 --> 00:04:16,435
Any plans to get married soon?

55
00:04:20,229 --> 00:04:21,151
Pardon?

56
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:22,834
Getting married.

57
00:04:23,383 --> 00:04:25,083
Do you have any plans to?

58
00:04:27,030 --> 00:04:29,035
Doesn’t matter if you marry
a woman or a man.

59
00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:31,631
You know I don’t mind that kind of thing.

60
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:35,265
It’d give me some peace of mind to know
you have someone nice

61
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,114
to take care of you.

62
00:04:38,062 --> 00:04:41,531
It’s only been a while
since I became the CEO,

63
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,939
I don’t think I have time
for a relationship right now.

64
00:04:44,338 --> 00:04:47,042
You don’t have time for a relationship?

65
00:04:47,042 --> 00:04:49,944
I was watching that show,
Bangkok Gossip,

66
00:04:49,944 --> 00:04:51,352
and they said you’ve been dating,

67
00:04:51,352 --> 00:04:52,109
who is it…

68
00:04:52,284 --> 00:04:55,629
An actor whose name starts with J.

69
00:04:57,301 --> 00:04:59,391
I broke up with him, Auntie.

70
00:04:59,391 --> 00:05:01,542
There’s no reason not to
find someone new.

71
00:05:01,542 --> 00:05:02,460
I’m sure it’s not beyond your ability.

72
00:05:02,784 --> 00:05:04,253
But I think—

73
00:05:04,253 --> 00:05:06,535
Just do it for Grandpa’s peace of mind.

74
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:10,660
Of course.

75
00:05:11,558 --> 00:05:13,922
Da Zhan, take this as an example, love.

76
00:05:14,071 --> 00:05:16,143
Don’t be stubborn like your cousin Pai.

77
00:05:16,268 --> 00:05:18,248
He can’t even make Grandpa happy.

78
00:05:18,248 --> 00:05:18,842
Grandpa.

79
00:05:18,842 --> 00:05:19,342
Hmm?

80
00:05:19,342 --> 00:05:21,935
Don’t you want to see me
married and settled, too?

81
00:05:21,935 --> 00:05:23,168
You were only asking Pai.

82
00:05:23,168 --> 00:05:24,442
How could you get married, North?

83
00:05:24,442 --> 00:05:26,107
You’re a child.

84
00:05:26,431 --> 00:05:28,033
Just stay with Grandpa for now.

85
00:05:28,358 --> 00:05:31,698
Wait a few more years,
and if you want to get married,

86
00:05:32,022 --> 00:05:34,104
I’ll be on board.

87
00:05:34,478 --> 00:05:36,109
You promise, Grandpa?

88
00:05:36,259 --> 00:05:37,466
Thank you.

89
00:05:38,015 --> 00:05:38,975
Speaking of which…

90
00:05:40,074 --> 00:05:42,773
Don’t you want your cousin to teach you
the ropes of our trade, North?

91
00:05:48,614 --> 00:05:49,434
I…

92
00:05:49,609 --> 00:05:50,954
I think I…

93
00:05:51,428 --> 00:05:54,863
I want to try and learn to do business

94
00:05:55,737 --> 00:05:56,834
on my own.

95
00:05:58,993 --> 00:05:59,894
How so?

96
00:06:02,565 --> 00:06:03,405
Well…

97
00:06:04,304 --> 00:06:05,674
I actually…

98
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,674
I have an idea…

99
00:06:11,849 --> 00:06:13,679
My friend and I want to open a bakery.

100
00:06:13,879 --> 00:06:15,219
Please, Grandpa?

101
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:19,924
Well, I don’t see why not.

102
00:06:19,924 --> 00:06:23,001
Oh, I love you so much, Grandpa.

103
00:06:23,001 --> 00:06:23,798
Thank you.

104
00:06:43,193 --> 00:06:45,997
I’ve placed your new suit in your office, sir.

105
00:06:45,997 --> 00:06:48,790
You have an interview with Fobes
at half past noon.

106
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:51,069
I have drafted some answers
for you for the interview.

107
00:06:51,069 --> 00:06:53,013
There’s a board meeting at 2 p.m.

108
00:06:53,013 --> 00:06:55,909
And at 7 p.m., a one-hour call
with our Khon Khaen branch.

109
00:06:55,909 --> 00:06:57,796
After that, you have dinner with Mr. Win.

110
00:06:57,796 --> 00:06:59,766
I’ve rescheduled it for 8.30 p.m.

111
00:06:59,766 --> 00:07:00,937
What do you think, Mr. Pai?

112
00:07:05,530 --> 00:07:06,808
Why did we reschedule?

113
00:07:07,157 --> 00:07:09,662
Uh, I thought you might be too tired.

114
00:07:11,284 --> 00:07:12,099
It’s alright.

115
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:13,263
It’s just dinner.

116
00:07:13,263 --> 00:07:14,269
Let’s not inconvenience him.

117
00:07:16,041 --> 00:07:17,876
Are you alright?

118
00:07:18,126 --> 00:07:19,049
You’re panting.

119
00:07:19,823 --> 00:07:20,645
Oh, no.

120
00:07:20,795 --> 00:07:22,089
I am not panting.

121
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:39,027
Ouch!

122
00:07:41,323 --> 00:07:42,000
Yes!

123
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,823
Ugh, I’m not playing with you anymore!

124
00:07:44,048 --> 00:07:45,661
Oww.

125
00:07:51,057 --> 00:07:51,686
Dang it.

126
00:07:55,106 --> 00:07:55,901
Pure.

127
00:07:58,921 --> 00:08:00,248
Let’s open a bakery.

128
00:08:00,248 --> 00:08:00,797
What?

129
00:08:01,371 --> 00:08:03,264
What are you trying to do?

130
00:08:07,532 --> 00:08:09,412
Well, I…

131
00:08:11,609 --> 00:08:14,516
I want to try my hands at small business.

132
00:08:15,015 --> 00:08:15,660
Small?

133
00:08:16,783 --> 00:08:21,720
What about your hair salon, car wash, Labubus, and photo booth?

134
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,098
- Ugh!
- Huh?

135
00:08:23,298 --> 00:08:26,688
There’s no point dwelling on
what’s in the past, you know?

136
00:08:27,112 --> 00:08:29,583
We should focus on something positive.

137
00:08:38,990 --> 00:08:39,753
Fine!

138
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:45,557
Grandpa wants me to work with Pai,
but I don’t want to.

139
00:08:45,557 --> 00:08:49,002
The bakery is just an excuse
for me to get out of it.

140
00:08:49,351 --> 00:08:52,418
Now that sounds more like you.

141
00:08:56,387 --> 00:08:57,946
Let’s do it anyway.

142
00:08:57,946 --> 00:09:00,934
Help me be free from my cousin
for at least the next two years.

143
00:09:01,059 --> 00:09:01,902
Honestly?

144
00:09:02,301 --> 00:09:05,209
I don’t understand you and your cousin.

145
00:09:05,758 --> 00:09:09,322
One is an all-rounded gentleman.

146
00:09:09,322 --> 00:09:10,807
The other is…

147
00:09:11,706 --> 00:09:12,811
Handsome?

148
00:09:12,811 --> 00:09:13,801
A loser!

149
00:09:13,801 --> 00:09:14,601
Watch it.

150
00:09:18,995 --> 00:09:20,324
But to tell you the truth,

151
00:09:21,572 --> 00:09:24,171
I can’t even blame Pai.

152
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:27,386
It was my bad luck that my parents
both died right after I was born,

153
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:29,084
and I had to live with Pai.

154
00:09:30,407 --> 00:09:33,107
Why don’t you just try to be nice to him?

155
00:09:35,378 --> 00:09:36,723
He stresses me the hell out.

156
00:09:36,723 --> 00:09:37,619
He’s such a stickler.

157
00:09:38,143 --> 00:09:40,729
He gives me an earful
for even the smallest mistakes.

158
00:09:41,278 --> 00:09:41,942
Gives me goosebumps.

159
00:09:50,703 --> 00:09:51,450
Please?

160
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,099
Fine.

161
00:09:55,249 --> 00:09:55,917
Yes!

162
00:09:57,988 --> 00:09:59,261
I’m due for a date.

163
00:09:59,386 --> 00:10:00,132
Bye.

164
00:10:00,631 --> 00:10:01,440
Oh.

165
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,876
You’re just gonna run off, huh?

166
00:10:06,146 --> 00:10:07,922
Another business failure incoming.

167
00:10:26,281 --> 00:10:31,604
(Photos from Grandpa Soepohn’s birthday party shot by Da Zhan.)

168
00:10:38,524 --> 00:10:41,474
JEERAMONKOLTHANUN

169
00:10:58,137 --> 00:10:58,826
Nana.

170
00:11:00,698 --> 00:11:01,475
Ms. Nana.

171
00:11:04,221 --> 00:11:04,991
Ms. Nana!

172
00:11:04,991 --> 00:11:06,298
Y–Yes, sir!

173
00:11:06,298 --> 00:11:07,339
I already got it done.

174
00:11:09,361 --> 00:11:10,996
I’m going on a walk.

175
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,086
I’ll finish the rest of the work afterward.

176
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:15,119
Why don’t you go home and rest?

177
00:11:15,668 --> 00:11:16,836
Are you sure, sir?

178
00:12:17,643 --> 00:12:18,359
Hello.

179
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:20,030
Hello.

180
00:12:22,002 --> 00:12:25,953
I… dropped my car key into this pond.

181
00:12:26,377 --> 00:12:30,367
I don’t know what the owner of this place was thinking to put so many ponds in here.

182
00:12:31,415 --> 00:12:33,482
Maybe they believed
their feng shui master so much

183
00:12:33,482 --> 00:12:35,326
that they forgot to think about
customers’ safety.

184
00:12:37,203 --> 00:12:38,203
I guess so.

185
00:12:38,702 --> 00:12:39,441
Oh.

186
00:12:40,514 --> 00:12:41,361
I’m Tim.

187
00:12:41,536 --> 00:12:42,736
I’m an architect.

188
00:12:42,861 --> 00:12:45,165
I was here to meet my client about
interior design.

189
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:46,511
We lost track of time while talking.

190
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:48,582
Next thing we knew, the mall was closed.

191
00:12:50,529 --> 00:12:51,446
I’m Pai.

192
00:12:53,143 --> 00:12:54,590
Do you work here, Mr. Pai?

193
00:12:56,063 --> 00:12:57,350
You can say that.

194
00:12:58,124 --> 00:13:00,744
Your boss must be really harsh

195
00:13:01,068 --> 00:13:03,781
to lock you in here
and make you work well into the night.

196
00:13:04,255 --> 00:13:05,105
I’m happy to do it.

197
00:13:20,578 --> 00:13:24,300
Did you find your key?

198
00:13:24,825 --> 00:13:25,591
No.

199
00:13:48,584 --> 00:13:51,114
You fell down because
you were helping me.

200
00:13:51,688 --> 00:13:54,375
I couldn’t possibly let you
get in here alone, could I?

201
00:14:05,142 --> 00:14:06,891
Or we can just go crazy?

202
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:08,245
Tim!

203
00:14:10,492 --> 00:14:11,381
There!

204
00:14:11,830 --> 00:14:12,598
Pai!

205
00:14:13,022 --> 00:14:14,103
We’re not children.

206
00:14:14,502 --> 00:14:16,259
Who would even do that?

207
00:14:17,407 --> 00:14:18,794
You started it.

208
00:14:18,794 --> 00:14:20,349
You splashed me first.

209
00:14:22,066 --> 00:14:22,870
Tim!

210
00:14:24,318 --> 00:14:25,295
Take that!

211
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,147
Mr. Tim?

212
00:14:31,843 --> 00:14:33,042
Are you alright?

213
00:14:44,799 --> 00:14:46,311
Gotcha!

214
00:15:03,411 --> 00:15:05,383
3-58 is over there.

215
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:08,399
Thank you so much, Mr. Pai.

216
00:15:08,573 --> 00:15:11,414
If it weren’t for you, I’m afraid
I might have to sleep here at this mall.

217
00:15:13,735 --> 00:15:14,975
Aren’t you going home?

218
00:15:15,699 --> 00:15:19,077
Please don’t tell me your boss
really does lock you in here.

219
00:15:19,227 --> 00:15:21,671
Tell me if that’s the case. I’m reporting
your boss to the Ministry of Labor.

220
00:15:23,443 --> 00:15:27,571
Actually… I own this place.

221
00:15:30,267 --> 00:15:31,565
Ah…

222
00:15:33,911 --> 00:15:36,404
This is like one of those micro-dramas.

223
00:15:37,053 --> 00:15:39,959
About what I said earlier at the fountain
and other stuff,

224
00:15:40,483 --> 00:15:41,751
I’m really sorry.

225
00:15:41,751 --> 00:15:42,646
It’s alright.

226
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:46,048
I’m not a big fan of the fountain
in that particular area myself.

227
00:15:46,048 --> 00:15:48,273
But I really couldn’t go against
my family’s feng shui master.

228
00:15:50,070 --> 00:15:53,318
Well, then I guess
you need to take responsibility.

229
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:58,161
For making a customer like me fall…

230
00:15:58,161 --> 00:15:59,094
into the water.

231
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:07,042
Maybe a meal?

232
00:16:10,661 --> 00:16:12,639
I’m not sure if I have time.

233
00:16:12,963 --> 00:16:14,020
It’s alright.

234
00:16:14,020 --> 00:16:15,795
Whenever that’s convenient for you.

235
00:16:15,795 --> 00:16:18,646
Maybe next time, or even the next.

236
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,094
Just please don’t turn me down.

237
00:16:34,466 --> 00:16:36,895
It’s a bit damp, but please take it.

238
00:16:49,034 --> 00:16:50,578
I’d better go.

239
00:16:51,551 --> 00:16:52,402
Goodnight.

240
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,428
Goodnight.

241
00:17:38,831 --> 00:17:42,823
TIM THANIN CHAIYANUWAT
“THE HANDSOME AND YUMMY
ARCHITECT”

242
00:18:17,312 --> 00:18:19,415
Of all the posts I accidentally liked…

243
00:18:19,939 --> 00:18:21,442
What is he going to think of me?

244
00:18:33,355 --> 00:18:35,560
ONE WEEK LATER

245
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,699
My goal in this trimester is

246
00:18:37,699 --> 00:18:41,515
to attract popular brands online
as our main selling point

247
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,664
to create a flow in our mall’s traffic.

248
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:49,398
If you have any more questions,
I’m only one call away.

249
00:18:51,395 --> 00:18:52,263
Thank you.

250
00:18:52,263 --> 00:18:53,599
Thank you for trusting me.

251
00:19:08,691 --> 00:19:09,433
Mr. Pai. 

252
00:19:10,282 --> 00:19:11,104
Mr. Pai. 

253
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:12,649
Mr. Pai, sir.

254
00:19:12,649 --> 00:19:13,253
Yes?

255
00:19:13,977 --> 00:19:16,839
The new zone we’ve been planning,
where would you like it to be?

256
00:19:16,839 --> 00:19:18,027
On the first floor.

257
00:19:18,476 --> 00:19:20,408
Let’s take a look at it, shall we?

258
00:19:21,182 --> 00:19:23,549
Nana, why don’t you take them there?

259
00:19:23,549 --> 00:19:24,477
I’ll be right behind you.

260
00:19:25,625 --> 00:19:26,637
Of course.

261
00:19:26,637 --> 00:19:27,689
This way, please.

262
00:19:34,727 --> 00:19:35,731
Mr. Tim.

263
00:19:36,605 --> 00:19:38,330
This is my personal contact.

264
00:19:38,704 --> 00:19:39,931
Would it be alright if I contact you romantically?
